OL,3,C'I went on a school trip to a stately
OL,4,Chome and ended up buying it'
OL,6,FHarrison, who was 15 at the time, was
OL,7,Fthe daughter of a Sheffield
OL,8,Fsteelworker. She "didn't like school
OL,9,Fthat much" and spent a lot of her time
OL,10,Fcaring for her mother, who had bone
OL,11,Fcancer and was paraplegic.
OL,13,FLife was very much hand-to-mouth.
OL,15,FShe said: "(To source) food, I used to
OL,16,Fmiss school on a Friday, go down and
OL,17,Fmeet my dad and would go around the
OL,18,Fmarket with a carrier bag and say (to
OL,19,Fthe stallhollders) 'hi mate, what have
OL,20,Fyou got that you don't want?'"
