OL,3,C'I went on a school trip to a stately
OL,4,Chome and ended up buying it'
OL,6,FLittle did she know at the time that
OL,7,Fher visit to Thornbridge would prove
OL,8,Flife-changing.
OL,10,F"I saw this incredible place and I
OL,11,Fthought, I need to live here," she
OL,12,Fsays. "And guess what - I do.
OL,14,F"I wake up every morning, open the
OL,15,Fcurtains and go, 'what happened?'"
OL,17,FMore than 40 years after that school
OL,18,Ftrip, Harrison and her husband, Jim,
OL,19,Fnow own Thornbridge Hall, which sits
OL,20,Fin the heart of the Peak District.
